---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const lastUpdated = "July 13, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — VoltForge"
  description="VoltForge Privacy Policy: what data we collect, how we use it, and your rights. VoltForge does not sell personal data and does not collect build configurations."
  noIndex={false}
>
  <div class="legal-page">
    <div class="legal-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="badge badge-safe" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">Legal</div>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-body">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="legal-content">

          <div class="legal-summary card-accent">
            <strong>Plain-English Summary:</strong> VoltForge runs calculator logic in your browser.
            We do not store your build configurations. We use Plausible Analytics (privacy-preserving,
            no personal data). We show ads via Google AdSense and use Amazon/Newegg affiliate links.
            We do not sell your data. Ever.
          </div>

          <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
          <p>
            VoltForge (<strong>voltforge.app</strong>) is an independent website providing free PC power supply
            calculation tools, build cost estimators, and educational guides for PC builders.
            VoltForge is not affiliated with any hardware manufacturer, retailer, or component brand.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

          <h3>2.1 Information You Provide</h3>
          <p>
            When you use the Contact form on this website, we collect the information you voluntarily submit:
            your name, email address, and message content. This information is transmitted to our form
            processing service (Formspree) and used solely to respond to your inquiry.
          </p>

          <h3>2.2 Calculator Usage (Not Stored)</h3>
          <p>
            All calculator computations (component selections, PSU analysis, cost estimates) run
            entirely client-side in your web browser. <strong>VoltForge does not transmit or store
            your component selections or build configurations.</strong> When you share a build via URL,
            the build data is encoded in the URL itself — we do not store it server-side.
          </p>

          <h3>2.3 Analytics</h3>
          <p>
            VoltForge uses <strong>Plausible Analytics</strong> to understand aggregate traffic patterns
            (e.g., which pages are most visited, which countries visitors come from). Plausible is
            GDPR-compliant and does not use cookies, does not collect personally identifiable information,
            and does not track visitors across websites. No personal data is collected for analytics purposes.
          </p>

          <h3>2.4 Advertising (Google AdSense)</h3>
          <p>
            VoltForge displays advertisements served by <strong>Google AdSense</strong>. Google uses
            cookies and similar technologies to serve interest-based advertisements. Google's use of
            advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on your visit to this
            site and other sites on the internet. You may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting
            <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Ad Settings</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            VoltForge does not control the cookies placed by Google AdSense. Please review
            <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's Privacy Policy</a>
            for information on how they process data.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Affiliate Links</h2>
          <p>
            VoltForge participates in affiliate programs including Amazon Associates and the Newegg Affiliate Program.
            When you click a product link on VoltForge and make a purchase, we may earn a small commission
            at no additional cost to you. Affiliate participation does not influence our product recommendations —
            we recommend based on technical merit, not commission rates.
          </p>
          <p>
            Amazon and Newegg may use cookies to track affiliate referrals. Please review their respective
            privacy policies for details.
          </p>

          <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
          <p>VoltForge itself sets one first-party cookie/localStorage item:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>vf-theme</strong> (localStorage): stores your dark/light mode preference. Contains no personal data.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Third-party cookies may be set by Google AdSense. You can manage cookie preferences through
            your browser settings or an ad opt-out tool.
          </p>

          <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            Contact form submissions are retained for up to 12 months after your inquiry is resolved,
            then permanently deleted. We do not retain any other personal data.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Access personal data we hold about you</li>
            <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
            <li>Object to processing of your data</li>
          </ul>
          <p>To exercise these rights, contact us via the <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>.</p>

          <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            VoltForge does not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
            If you believe a child has provided us personal information, please contact us immediately
            so we can delete it.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top
            of this page reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of VoltForge after changes
            constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For privacy-related inquiries, please use our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
.legal-page {}
.legal-hero {
  padding: 4rem 0 2rem;
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-deep) 0%, var(--bg-primary) 100%);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
}
.legal-meta {
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
}
.legal-body {
  padding: 3rem 0 5rem;
}
.legal-content {
  max-width: 760px;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1.5rem;
}
.legal-content h2 {
  font-size: 1.375rem;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
  padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
}
.legal-content h3 {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  color: var(--text-primary);
}
.legal-content p {
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.75;
  max-width: 70ch;
}
.legal-content ul {
  padding-left: 1.5rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.4rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}
.legal-summary {
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}
</style>
